<subSubSection id="085B6D67DC1112FE7F8B288992121563" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="78835C7C504382E7F513DC4978A19E90" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FAF764711170B7CA3915D3E26F7F2187" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Separated from congeners by: an embolus that coils three times (vs. between four and five times); dRTA that is blunter and translucent (vs. more pointed); constriction between ST I and ST II absent (vs. present, female of 
<taxonomicName id="A009080E84D65FC8D1C534A6D394F91A" genus="G." lsidName="G. baueri" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="baueri">
<emphasis id="98BD4B5CAB06AE149F67951661DD7742" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">G. baueri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. unknown); carapace color with grayish tinge (dark brown to black, orangish or yellowish in congeners).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6B4A4B1166EC91FF6FD4196E57B0A945" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="B729575848FA62772F81FF07D29EAA64" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5BCEA445C05F1EF6B21E9E0CF503D78D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
